author: A Correspondent
title: Maharashtra emerge West Zone badminton champions
text:
Thomas Cupper Akshay Dewalkar was the star performer as Maharashtra rallied from 0-2 down to beat Madhya Pradesh 3-2 to clinch the senior team title in the West Zone inter-state badminton tourney, organised by Badminton Organisation of Raigadh and hosted by the DY Patil Sports Academy in Nerul yesterday.


The Maharashtra team after beating Madhya Pradesh 3-2 to win the senior team title of the West Zone inter-state badminton championships at DY Patil Sports Academy in Nerul yesterday 
Maharashtra lost their men's and women's singles with Harsheel Dani losing to Abhimanyu Singh and Neha Pandit beaten by junior India No 1 Shriyanshi Pardesh.
Akshay then won the men's doubles with Akshay Raut and the mixed doubles with Revati Devasthale after Mansi Gadgil and Vaishnavi Iyer won the women's doubles tie.
